PARENTS at Barcelona Primary School in Etwatwa, Ekurhuleni, are sick and tired of their kids sharing their learning space with rats. Their old mobile classrooms also have holes, which were dug by the rats. Daily Sun visited the school and found holes in the mobile classrooms, which had become home to rats and cockroaches. The parents said their kids were forced to study in this environment as they had been neglected by the Gauteng Department of Education. “We protested several times and even went to the department’s offices to hand over a memorandum, but we are still ignored,” said gogo Tshidi Nyembe. The parents said they were being taken for fools by the department. ALSO READ | SANParks sacks CEO Fundisile Mketeni! They said Gauteng education MEC Panyaza Lesufi promised them a new school after they protested over learning conditions at the school. “MEC Panyaza Lesufi came to this school in 2017 and personally promised that he would build us a new school in 2018 but years later, not even a foundation has been laid,” said gogo Tshidi. She was speaking on behalf of the parents, who vowed not to stop protesting until the department delivered on its promises.  In 2017, gogo Tshidi stripped and sat on top of a bucket to show how their kids were using the unhygienic bucket system. ALSO READ | Senior journalist turned Shakes Mashaba’s taxi
driver This pushed Lesufi to visit the school, where he promised them a school and new toilets. After the story was published, the school’s old flushing toilets were unblocked. Gauteng education spokesman Steve Mabona said they were aware of the problem and were waiting for information from the Department of Infrastructure Development. He said they discovered the area where the school is located was not zoned.